statement:
Let R_0 be a discrete valuation ring with fraction field K and residue field k. The square
\[
\begin{CD}
Shv_{\mathrm{Nilp}}(\operatorname{Bun}_{G,K}) @>\mathsf L^{\mathrm{restr}}_{G,\mathrm{coarse}}>> QCoh(\mathrm{LS}^{\mathrm{restr}}_{\check G,K})\\
@V\mathrm{Sp}_{K\to k}VV @VV\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{QCoh}}_{K\to k}V \\
Shv_{\mathrm{Nilp}}(\operatorname{Bun}_{G,k}) @>\mathsf L^{\mathrm{restr}}_{G,\mathrm{coarse}}>> QCoh(\mathrm{LS}^{\mathrm{restr}}_{\check G,k})
\end{CD}
\]
canonically commutes, where $\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{QCoh}}_{K\to k}$ denotes derived base change along $\mathrm{LS}^{\mathrm{restr}}_{\check G,K}\to \mathrm{LS}^{\mathrm{restr}}_{\check G,k}$.
